------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objective

The objective of this exercise is to help learners apply Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) concepts to a real-world scenario by:

Creating a class with an initial state
Modifying an objectâ€™s data using methods
Understanding how object methods affect internal attributes
Practicing class instantiation and method calls

This exercise reinforces the concepts of encapsulation, attributes, methods, and object interaction in OOP.

Instructions

Create a class called BankAccount.
Add the following methods with an attribute balance initialized to zero:
deposit() which adds an amount to the balance.
withdraw() which subtracts an amount from the balance.
display_balance() which displays the current balance.
Test the class by creating an account, depositing and withdrawing amounts, then displaying the final balance.
